comm: good length and slanted across the off stump, Warner simply watches it through to Watling
Warner yells "wait on" as he stands tall to this short ball and punches straight to mid-off
Warner yells "wait on" again. He presses forward to this very full one outside off and drives straight to mid-off
good length, 135.7ks, seaming away off the surface. Warner gropes and misses outside off
slanting into the pads, picked up and flicked to square-ish long leg
very full and outside off, 137.9ks, Finch moves forward, gets closer to the pitch and push-drives it in the gap between extra cover and mid-off
good length and angling away outside off, gets forward and pushes the ball to mid-off
very full and outside off, Finch gets his front foot moving again. Tapped to the left of mid-off for another single

and this outside edge flies just wide of Neesham at second slip. The fielder dives full-length to his left and just finger-tips it away. Good length, angled in, and bends away outside off, takes the outside edge. Warner pushes at it away from the body, and gets away
even fuller and angled in, defended back to the bowler
back of a length, angled in, the swings away, a thick outside edge streaks away to point
full and largely holds its line in the channel, Warner covers his off stump and shoulders arms
good length and hurtles back in, top-of-off line, inches forward and plays it back to the bowler
very full and outside off, moves forward again, good stride, tapped into the covers
Williamson dives to his right from mid-off, and stops this stroke. Full and outside off, front-foot drive down the ground
very full on middle, push-driven straight down the ground, Warner did not over-hit it. Williamson moves back and to his left from mid-off to cut this off
bouncer outside off, bursts off the surface, Finch lets it go outside off. Watling leaps and takes the ball over his head
back of a length and ducks back in off the surface, Finch plays across the line. He is caught on the move. Off the top of the pad, and lobs in front of second slip
Warner steps out and across, Boult shortens his length and gets it to swing in. Bounces over a fourth stump down leg. Leg-side wide
dug short and outside off, shimmies out again, pushed to the covers
back of a length and outside off, punched to cover
short of a length, Finch is on the move again, hopping and failing to make contact with a flick
good length and swings back in slightly, Finch attempts a crease-bound cut and is beaten. Boult goes through the gate
jabbed into the covers
back of a length, 140.3ks, swerves back into Finch again. He is on the move again. Rapped on the thigh. The batsman was playing across and late on the shot too

that's a gem from Henry. Beats the outside, and nearly shaves the off stump. Too good to even kiss the edge, too good to even kiss the stump. Good length - shapes like an inswinger - pitches on leg, and then viciously seams away, opening up the left-hander. That's the magic ball
back of a length and outside off, leaps and jabs to the covers
blasted through mid-off. Full - not a half-volley outside off - gets forward and flat-bats it with all his might down the ground
back of a length on leg stump, slightly cramps him for room. Fended to midwicket
just short of a good length and outside off, chopped to cover
fuller and outside off, flat-bats a drive in the air, drops in front of cover
back of a length and outside off, swatted with a flat bat to mid-off
short and wide outside off, Finch jumps all over it, cracking a cut between point and the covers
short, comes back in a bit, attempts a flick, takes the pad, and lobs wide of the slips
back of a length and slanting away, dabbed to point from outside off
full and outside off, gets forward and pushes it to Williamson at extra cover
short and angled down leg, past the glance
Finch hits through the line and lofts a four. Good length and outside off, takes it on the up and drills it over mid-off
short on the leg stump, 139.9ks, flapped away square through the leg side
pretty full on off, defended
good length on off, forward and firmly punched to mid-off
short and angled in on off, hops and pushes down to mid-on
dug short and outside off, 140ks, Warner read the length early. Skipping back and nailing a pull over square leg. Kumar Dharmasena swerves out of the way, and evades it
low full-toss outside off, punched straight to mid-off
Warner runs down the track, shows the ace early. Banged in on middle, Warner leaps and forces the ball to the covers
back of a length and swings in, Finch aims a cut, and drags an inside edge to midwicket
pitched further up, and angling away outside off, Finch covers his off stump and lets it be

an appeal for leg-before from Boult. He chats with Williamson. The time's up. Back of a length and swings back in, Finch leaps and is struck above the knee-roll. That's definitely missing the stumps. It pitched outside leg and darted in, and was sailing over the stumps
veering into the leg stump, off the pad and rolls behind square
short and just outside off, short-armed away to square leg
full and wide outside off, Warner throws his hands at it and carves it up and over point. Warner's feet were stapled to the crease
back of a length and outside off, flat-batted to the covers
big bouncer outside off, Finch drops his wrists on it.  Wide called by the square-leg umpire
pitches outside off and nips away outside off, Finch is on the move as he drives and is lavishly beaten
good length and seams away outside off, Finch is on the move again. He drives and sends an outside edge flying to the left of first slip. Just one slip in place
full and in the channel, left alone now
another bouncer outside off, Finch is upright as the ball soars over him to Watling. Second wide of the over
glanced off the pads to fine leg
full and angled into the leg stump, diverted to square leg
short on the stumps, stabbed back to the bowler
back of a length and comes back in on off stump, hops and forces the ball wide of mid-on
short and outside off, 137ks, Warner controls a pull to deep square leg
back of a length and outside off, jabbing punch to extra cover
short of a good length and angling away outside off, Finch leans back and square-cuts away
slides a short ball across the batsman, cut away but straight to point
just short of Neesham at short third man. Too full for the cut, Warner still went through with it and managed to get a thick edge that raced past the man there for a boundary
gets to the pitch of the ball and hammers it straight to Williamson at cover
this is much better, slower through the air and lands it at length on middle, Warner stretches forward and blocks
flatter one on middle and leg, worked with the spin to midwicket
worked off his hip to square leg. Warner's just played a series of dots. Wow
length ball that slides into middle and leg, worked to mid-on as they sneak in a single. Warner trusted his partner's call and took off in a jiffy
digs a short ball into the body, not alarming bounce, neither was the pace that threatening. Warner gets on top of the bounce and deflects it wide of square leg
half-volley on the pads, flicked with the angle to deep fine leg. The fielder there didn't have to move an inch
back of length delivery on off stump, he hops back and bunts it to short cover
superb hand-eye coordination. Picks the length so early. Stayed back in the crease, waited for it and flayed it behind point. Those wrists. Superb. Square third man was a mere spectator.
drifts this back into middle and leg, Finch attempts a sweep and manages a glove. The keeper fluffs a relatively simple chance. Wide called
tossed up on middle, he gets forward and pats it to the off side

so the dropped chance didn't cost them much. Finch looks to play a predetermined sweep. Was across a long way even before the ball was delivered, so he was in no position to sweep that full delivery. He swung through way too early as well as the ball sneaked through to crash into the leg stump. Timely wicket for New Zealand. Australia were starting to run away with this.
some purchase off the pitch. This one turn's away from off stump, but Smith is half forward as he defends
worked off his hip to deep square and gets off the mark
steps out but can't get to the pitch of the ball, dabbed back down the pitch
worked with the spin to long-on for an easy single
length ball angling away, bunted wide of cover
short of length delivery around the sixth stump outside off, Smith watches it through to the keeper
delightful straight drive. Too full and the confidence from the first ODI speaks. He shuffles across just a touch and drills it down the ground past mid-on. Super timing
gets across and squeezes this full delivery to Williamson at cover
this is too full, he doesn't get underneath it. Jams his bat down to keep that out though
excellent stop by the skipper. Throws himself to his left to pull off a one-handed stop. That was travelling, saved three runs.
drifting into middle and leg, worked off his hip past square leg
gets across and wrists that one to midwicket
flighted over his eye line on middle, Warner eases it back past the bowler as they jog the single
this is fired full on middle from around the stumps, he stretches forward and blocks
makes a bit of room and punches that in-drifter to long-off
solid wrist work again as he eases it to wide long-on for an easy single to keep strike. Sensible stuff
full delivery angling away, squeezed between cover and point
this one nips away off the seam from length outside off, left alone
hops across to punch it into the gap at point, but this one jags back in to hit the inside edge and roll to the leg side
this is superb from Southee. This one's pitched up. The ball deviates away a wee bit, and Smith watches it through to the keeper
shapes to cut but realises the ball's too full for him to slash, lets it go instead
gets half-forward and bunts it towards cover, which is a little deep, and they get a single easily
eased with the spin to long-off, too full from Santner on that occasion
steps out but this one drifts away to beat the flick and hit him on the right thigh. Excellent from Santner. That's more like it.
gets to the pitch of the ball and dabs a tossed up delivery back down to the bowler
quicker one on middle and leg, tucked to square leg
slow turn back in, Warner was standing outside leg in anticipation of a full ball, just works it wide of square leg this time
shaped to drive but ended up defending solidly once he realised he was beaten in flight
low full toss, Warner could have actually swung across but instead waits and waits for it and ends up nearly yorking himself as he digs that out
mistimes an attempted drive to short cover. Pressure building? This has been an excellent comeback. Warner's timing has suddenly gone awry
once again no control whatsoever with that pull, just lobbed past the vacant square leg region
the ball stops on him a touch as he looks to drive firmly, gets a thick inside edge back to the bowler
punched to Williamson's right at cover, they manage to pinch a run
check-drives to cover. This one's bowled at length, once again looked like the ball stopped on him a touch
eased with the spin to long-off as they jog the single

sweeps and gets a bottom edge which is enough to beat short fine leg. Half-century for him, not a typically robust innings but he'll still take it. Coming back to the fielding effort, it could have been a better one from Trent Boult. Shouldn't have been more than two.
worked wide of short fine leg
short and wide, he rocks back and cracks it into the gap at deep point
gives it generous amount of flight on off, Smith gets forward and blocks
drifts in from wide of the crease, Smith bunts it to mid-off, where a misfield allows a single that shouldn't have been
floats a length ball on middle and leg, turned to midwicket
driven firmly to mid-on, tight line on middle
gets across and whips it to deep midwicket. Smith's get-off-strike shot, says Mark Taylor.
angles a full delivery in from around the stumps, pushed to cover. Calls 'no' immediately
hint of width, punched to sweeper cover
angles a length ball into middle and leg, worked wide of midwicket as they jog the single
nicely tossed up, shuffles across and glances to short fine leg
flatter on middle and leg, hangs back and works the ball through square leg
just short of a good length on middle stump, Warner steps outside leg and cuts out to sweeper cover. Brings up Australia's 100
Santner runs this length ball into Smith, who shuffles across and tucks around the corner
flatter and angled across, drills a drive to sweeper
non-turning length ball on off, dabbed towards midwicket for another single
back of a length and outside off, shuffles across and bunts it through square leg
flicked away through square leg
short and angled in on off from around the wicket, Warner camps back and fends it back to de Grandhomme
full and outside off, opens the face and glides the ball to point, where Guptill fumbles. NZ's fielding has been sloppy again
just short of a good length and angled in, glanced behind square
shortish and outside off, steered square through the off side
flatter and quicker on middle and leg, hangs back and whips through midwicket
Santner gives this more air, the line is on middle, smoothly driven down to long-on
tossed full on middle, played back to the bowler
back of a length and slides in, back-foot punch back to Santner
slower through the air, Santner held this back, hint of turn. Blocked to cover on the front foot
looped up around off, opens the face, and dabs it to extra cover. Smith is ready to chance a single, is isn't there, and Warner rightly sends his captain back
and Warner greets him with a lofted hit or rather a sliced hit. Full and wide outside off, drops to one knee, and toe-ends the ball over extra cover
back of a length on middle, worked deftly to the left of mid-on
short and outside off from over the wicket, hip-high ball, 133.1ks, Smith has ample time to swat-pull it away to the right of diving midwicket
full and outside off, walks across, and flicks to midwicket
just short of a good length and outside off, Warner brings out a smart late-cut. Hit to third man
shortish and outside off, check-pushed towards the cover-point region
good length on middle, clipped to midwicket
slides on middle, not that short, backs away and chops to Neesham at short third man
full, tossed up on middle, push-driven to mid-off
beats wide mid-off diving to his left. Tossed up, Warner twinkles down the track and drives it handsomely down the ground
worked off the pads through square leg
angled into the pads, tickled with the angle to short fine leg
hip-high short ball on off stump, Warner lays into it. Pulling it in the air over midwicket on the front foot
full and outside off, square-driven to Guptill at point
just short of a good length and outside off, swatted with a flat bat to mid-on
back of a length and outside off, punched to the right of extra cover, and to the left of Guptill at point
short and outside off, Warner unleashes another powerful pull. This time he pivots on the back foot and smashes it in the air to the left of midwicket
much fuller and outside off, crisply driven to extra cover
flighted on middle, played back to the bowler
tucked off the pads through square leg
short and turning away, chopped away wide of backward point, Trent Boult runs across to his right. Stumbles, slides, and his foot was in contact with the ad boards while pulling the ball in
looped up outside off, driven more or less straight to sweeper cover
length ball, pushed into the covers
down the track and driven down to long-on
good length and angled in, worked to midwicket
floated up on middle, driven along the ground to wide long-off
hip-high short ball on off, Smith pulls early and bottom-edges it to square leg
and Warner beats Henry again, this time to his right from long leg. Just short of a good length and outside off, chopped away fine of long leg
too straight in line, flicked to deep midwicket
pitched up and outside off, fluently driven to deep cover
back of a length and angled in, clipped to midwicket
short and outside off, forced away to deep point
back of a length and angled in, stands tall and punches it to mid-on
nice and full outside off, eased to deep cover
tickled off the pads, short fine leg (Southee) dives to his right to stop the ball
good length and angled in, worked to square leg. Good spell from Santner: 10-0-47-1
back of a length and outside off, Warner aims a late-cut, the ball grazes the outside edge and rolls to third man
back of a length and outside off, punched to point
driven with laser-guided precision. Beats extra cover to his left and mid-off to his right. Sublime placement. Floated full and outside off, caressed
back of a length and outside off, glided to point
tucked off the pads through square leg
back of a length and outside off, helped down to third man with an angled bat
full on the pads, flicked with an air of disdain. Split deep square and fine leg perfectly. Big boundary there, but it didn't matter.
width and he's crashed that behind point. Top class effort from Latham to run around at least 20 yards to his right and throw himself full stretch to stop that. Saved two
punched on the up sweeper cover
that's a hit! Wow, straight as a dye. The bowler had no time to even put his foot out. Such ferocity in his batting. Too full and he gave it the treatment.
full and tailing away from middle, squeezed back down the pitch
eased down to long-on, briefly thought of a second but he hit that too well.
slower and fuller on the pads, Warner misses a faint tickle to get him through to the century. Deflects off the pad to the keeper
looks to flay that through cover, gets it off the bottom of the bat and to the man on the edge of the ring. Cry of anguish as he executed the stroke

slower delivery on off, squeeze back down the pitch to get to the hundred. There's a typical leap, the joy is writ large on his face. His third hundred in five ODI innings. Can he convert this into a daddy hundred?
short and wide outside off, eased behind point as they jog the single
doesn't get the placement right this time. Slow off-cutter that has been hit straight to cover point
play and a miss. Not much width to play the cut. That kept a touch low as well and went through.
dabs a length ball on off towards short third man
forced off the backfoot to sweeper cover
worked off his pads wide of midwicket for a quick single
delicate little late dab to third man
angles a length ball into middle and leg, tucked between midwicket and square leg
uppish but into the gap, gets it down to sweeper cover. There's a half-century for the skipper. Muted celebration.
gets a thick inside edge that flies past leg stump and down to third man
gets in position early and pulls the short ball to deep square leg

the length ball nips back in from outside off, Smith played outside the line as he looked to ease it behind point. The ball missed everything. The appeal wasn't spontaneous either, and in the end, the right call has been made. No under-edge. Smith survives and rightly so
this has been clobbered over wide mid-on. Clears his front leg, and lofts the length ball over the infield without much fuss.
punched to deep cover as they pick an easy single again

poor effort from Matt Henry at third man. Dives full length but the timing is such that he had no chance despite that. Too full and wide, Warner did well to reach out and pick the bones out of that. Super placement
nips back in to hit him on the box. He went outside the line of the stumps to pull that behind square. He seems to be in some pain too and is flat on his back
went far too across to work that one away. The ball veered back in to hit him on the pad and deflect to the leg side
clobbered into cow corner, 20 rows back, maybe 25. Went across the stumps and swung through cleanly to get the elevation and distance. Hoisted away with a touch of arrogance
fetches the pull from outside off, gets it into the gap between deep square and deep midwicket
too full outside off, squeezed to deep point
makes room and bunts it wide of cover for a quick single

Boult floated this in at 135 clicks, it went to the deep midwicket fence at double that speed! One heck of a shot. Warner fetches the full ball from outside off and swings across the line. Super stuff.
too full outside off, squeezed to cover
low full toss on the pads, tickled into the fine leg boundary. Buffet bowling this, as Geoff Boycott would say. All he had to do to get a boundary was a faint deflection, which he did.
this one's full and straight on off stump, pushed to cover
beaten by pace. Looked to angle that length ball behind point but was late on the shot
pulled towards midwicket, not timed well but enough to get a single

the party's over. Good, low catch from Williamson at cover. This was full, Warner backed away and drilled it inside-out. Williamson stayed low and moved forward swiftly to take it inches from the ground. Applause, salutes for Warner. Super catch to end a super knock. Warner waited briefly for the no-ball check but eventually walks off.
beaten by a delivery that nibbles away from middle
hint of width, he opens the bat face late to steer it fine to third man
overbalanced but this was full and sliding down leg. Easy call for Paul Wilson
pulled from outside off towards deep midwicket
leading edge but falls short of mid-off, they sneak in a run though
wristy little flick down to long-on
hit high on the thigh pad as he looks to work it off his hip, they take a run off the deflection
super timing. The power of the bottom-hand. Flicks that superbly between midwicket and mid-on
whipped with the angle towards midwicket for a quick single
gets across the stumps and whips it uppishly towards square leg
digs one in short but Smith inside the line and helps it into the gap at fine leg. Easy pickings
down leg and it's tickled into the fine leg boundary again. Was there some pad? This one was drifting down, Smith hopped across and tickled it away fine.
Head's time to come to the party. Backs away and slaps that over the infield. The width was there and he muscled that away.
clean strike and a massive hit! Bleeding runs suddenly. Too full and angling into middle, Head stays inside the crease and slugs it over midwicket. Short boundary that side too
can't get any bat on that flick, deflects off the pad to the leg side as they steal a single

backs away and hammers it down the ground. The ball had passed the bowler even before he could react. Mid-off was inside the ring, so once it went past the bowler, it was four all the way. Sparkling batting this from the new batsman
cuts, but finds backward point

as easy as they come for Santner. This was a length ball outside off, Smith went across to play an agricultural heave but only managed to get the outside part of the bat to slice it to deep point. Not even the possibility of another century deterred him from playing his shots. End of a fine knock from the skipper!
crashed towards square third man. It was full and angling away, he opened the bat face late as he powered that away
gets a thick edge this time as he looks to cut, on the bounce to third man
right into the blockhole, manages to squeeze it out. There was half a shout for lbw but the ball would have missed leg stump. There was an inside edge too
gets the radar wrong, this one slips down the leg side. Southee appealed for caught behind. They've reviewed the decision, but there's no bat
the bottom of his bat chips off as he digs out an inswinging yorker.
yorker-length delivery on off, squeezed back to Southee who times his jump well to stop that

full and outside off, Head clears his front leg and hoists it down the ground, straight of long-off. Neesham over-runs the ball to his left, and concedes a four. Another example of sloppy fielding from NZ
pretty full on middle, Head bludgeons a drive to Williamson at extra cover. Marsh takes off, Head isn't keen on a single. Williamson can't effect a direct hit
off-stump yorker, dug out to wide long-off
low full-toss on off, pushed down to long-on, as Marsh gets off the mark after four balls

high full-toss outside off, umpire Dharmasena from square leg deems it a no-ball, above the waist. Outside off, Head gets forward, and slices a catch to extra cover. They go to the TV umpire, who confirms it was over waist-height. Umpire Wilson signals a free-hit
front-foot no-ball now. Tight call. Length and outside off, Marsh looks to smite it over the leg side, sends a thick outside edge flying to third man
hacked away to short fine leg leg off the inside half
full and angling away on a set of stumps outside off or even wider, Head has a wild swish at it and does not make contact
pretty full and outside off, Marsh goes very hard at the ball, loses his shape, and toe-ends a jab down to long-on
clears mid-on. Good length and outside off, slower cutter, swung off the bottom part of the bat over mid-on
Southee rolls his fingers across another cutter, 115ks, Head slashes early and misses
wild off-side wide
dances out, leans back and swings, and carves an outside edge wide of backward point
very full on off, squeezed off the toe end to deep midwicket
steps out, manufactures a full-toss, aims the covers, and ends up slicing it down to third man
full on middle, belted to Williamson at mid-off
pushed to mid-off for a risky single. A direct hit from de Grandhomme could have had Marsh at the non-striker's end
full on middle and leg, clears his front leg and clubs it with a cross bat to long-on

inswinging yorker, ends on leg stump, Marsh is late to bring his bat down. Off the pad and rolls to the covers. Head now is keen on a risky single. Marsh stays put. Boult runs across to his left. Attempts a back-handed flick, can't hit the stumps
very full on the stumps, jammed down to fine leg. The fielder runs in and collects the ball. Marsh chances the second and completes it. NZ needed a direct hit here too
wide yorker outside off, Marsh loses his shape as he aims to reach out. He falls over and is beaten
jabbed to the covers for one
Marsh backs away outside leg, the bowler follows him with a yorker. Dug back to the bowler
Marsh moves away outside leg again, Southee chases him and nails another yorker again. Pins him on his toes. Inside-edged. Impressive bowling
length ball outside off to Head, he crashes a drive down the ground. Williamson throws himself to his left from wide mid-off, but is beaten
overpitched and outside off, clears his front leg and violently drives the ball to deep cover
full on the stumps, whipped away to deep midwicket, on the bounce to the fielder
very full on middle, Head brings his fast hands into play. Pings it straight over the bowler's head. Umpire Wilson is forced to take evasive action. Ducks under it
very full on leg stump, whipped towards square leg
Neesham runs to his left from long-on, but the ball sails over his outstretched hand. Marsh races down the track, takes it on the half-volley and hoists it down the ground
pretty full, flat-batted past the bowler
cutter from the back of the hand, drifts down leg. They sneak in a bye too
full on the stumps, driven to long-on. They put pressure on Neesham, take him on, and collect two. Little fumble from the fielder in the deep
a bit overpitched and outside off, holds his shape, drilling a drive to the right of mid-off
back-to-back half-centuries for Head. Full and outside off, driven down the ground
steps out, takes a full-toss and tonks it to long-on
near yorker outside off, jabbed down to Williamson at wide mid-off
Marsh moves outside leg, clears his front leg, this is full, following him. Belts a drive to long-on
slower ball, parcelled up, and dispatched over the cow corner boundary. 119ks, Head steps out, adjusts, takes it from off stump and mows it into the crowd
caught at backward point. Full and wide outside off, Head throws his hands at the ball. Slices a catch to Munro at backward point, who clasps it in front of his face
very full on middle, whipped to cow corner
yorker on off or just outside off, squirted back to the bowler
full and outside off, hit down to long-off
full ball on off, Marsh sizes it up, stays back and blasts it over long-off
very full on middle, whipped to Santner at long-on
back of a length and outside off, pulled in the air over midwicket
slower short ball, 110ks, offcutter, slogs early and is hoodwinked
follows the cutter with a yorker on off, jammed back to the bowler
another slower short ball outside off, Marsh does not pick it again. Slogs blindly and does not make contact
Marsh picks this full-toss up and puts it over long-on. Caught in the crowd. Low full-toss on off, Marsh smites it down the ground
cutter, slower one floats past the leg stump as Marsh does not connect with the slog
full-toss over the waist, slower ball, pulled away to deep square leg
114.3ks slower short one outside off, Wade was sitting back, waiting for it. Muscles it over the midwicket boundary
full on the leg stump, powered away between deep midwicket and long-on
yorker on off, shovelled away to long-on. Marsh hares across for the second. Australia get to 350
Marsh gets to a fifty off 33 balls. He races down the track, looks like a slower ball, bludgeoned over cow corner for a massive, massive six
short and wide outside off, carved away to deep point
bowled'em.  No celebration at all from NZ. Good length on middle, Wade eyes a cross-bat slog across the line. He does not touch it. Boult hits the stumps. Rare dot
full and sliding outside leg, he can't tickle it away. Off the pad and floats into the gloves of Watling

full-toss on middle, whipped away to wide long-on. They chance a second. The throw isn't accurate enough. Bailey dives full-length and is home by the time Henry collects the ball and tips the bails off
half-volley on off, clears his front leg, and launches it over long-off for another monster six
full again on middle and leg, right in the swinging slot, Marsh goes down the ground again. This is pasted over long-on
six, six, six. Strike three. Poor ball. Overpitched on middle, Marsh simply blasts it over long-on, replicating the previous hit
low full toss outside off, Marsh reaches out but can't connect. Past the tramline, Southee gets away
full and on off, Marsh eyes up the big slog again, can only manage an inside-edge onto the pad. The ball rolls towards cover.
starts off with a high full toss on middle, pushed to the off side

big appeal for lbw. Possibly, pad first? They decide against a review. The ball bends back in to beat him on the forward prod. The line was good, but there was some bat involved too. Good decision from Kumar Dharmasena
beats cover and point. Sublime timing. Just an extension of the arms as he powers the length ball into the gap. Superb timing.
crunching cover drive on the up. Nothing wrong with the delivery. If someone hits you through the infield like that, just stand up and applaud. Nice, high elbow, perfect balance. Delightful
another one that threads the infield, Warner and Smith give it chase and pull it back in the nick of time.
defends that length ball on middle from the crease
full and swinging away from outside off, driven firmly to cover
invites the drive by pitching this up full outside off, left alone
crashes it into the point boundary at the rate of knots. Sehwag would be proud of that! Key to playing that was picking the length early, which he did. Intent from Guptill
flicked imperiously into the deep midwicket boundary! This was a delicious leg-stump half-volley that got the treatment it deserved. He's raced away like a bullet train
punched back to the bowler
straight drive that could have been four if not for the bowler, who got a hand on it on his followthrough
firm push on the up to mid-off. Planted his front foot forward to play that stroke
uppish but down to third man. Backed away to cut but was cramped for room
full and sliding down leg, Latham misses a faint little tickle. Scoring opportunity missed. Wide called
solid defense. Gets half-forward and dabs that length ball gently to the off side
leans into the drive, plays it well but can't pick the gap. Straight to cover
gets on top of the bounce and defends it back down the pitch
rip roaring bouncer outside off, Latham does well to sway out of the way
rapped on the glove as the ball falls short of gully. Did well to take the glove off the bat handle as he hopped to defend. The ball reared up from length
angles back in to whizz past the thigh pad. Some exercise for the umpire
gets on top of the bounce and turns it to the leg side as they scamper a single.
gets a thick inside edge toward square leg as he shapes to drive. The ball deviated back in ever-so-slightly
solid defense to that short of length delivery outside off
leading edge but safe. Just short of the man coming in from short cover. They sneak in a run though.
back of length delivery on middle and leg, he gets onto his toes and tucks it towards square leg for a quick single
firm push but straight to cover
feeding him to his strengths. A length ball on middle and leg, chipped over midwicket. Didn't get the kind of timing he would have liked. Excellent running nevertheless to come back for three
gets half-forward and eases that short of length delivery to point
hurries him with a 143 clicks ball that snakes back in to have him hopping, pushed to cover
backs away and lofts him over the infield. Not quite off the middle but splits mid-off and mid-on.
not much room to work with, defends that away-going length ball to the off side
gets forward and stabs that one away towards point
once again can't find the gap, angles the length ball towards point

the pressure has told. He was unable to get the ball off the square and has now fallen to the softest of dismissals. Looks to work it to the on side, but closed the bat face early and ends up chipping a simple return catch.
works the incoming short of length delivery on middle and leg towards fine leg

whipped off his hip towards the man coming in from deep square, the throw went to the wrong end, but overthrows at the bowler's end means there's no damage done. Williamson was nearly halfway down the pitch when he had to turn back
starts off with a yorker length delivery outside off, squeezed to cover
has he broken his bat? It was full and he crashes that past mid-off. Geez, that was nowhere near the middle but it still travelled
just a hint of width and he's hit that on the rise again. Free flow of the bat as it comes down nicely. He's really timing them sweetly
another cracking sound off the wood as he defended that to mid-off. Phew
thumped down the ground but straight to mid-off again
sliding into the pads, worked to deep square
whipped off his hip towards deep square
excellent delivery that. Nips away off the seam from the length area outside off, left alone
nearly chopped back onto the stumps. Half-hearted push to a delivery that wasn't too far away from off stump. Bounced wide
gets forward and defends that incoming full delivery with a straight bat
gets this one to jag back in off the deck from outside off, left alone
firm push but straight to mid-off
shows the full face of the bat to defend that incoming short of length delivery
stands tall and punches that to short cover

beautiful delivery! Pat Cummins with a huge wicket with a delivery that had serious pace. 148.6kph . This one was full, it came back in from wide of the crease and then held its line as Guptill's poke took the thinnest of edges on the way through to Wade. Special ball that.
angles a length ball across Neesham, who gets on top of the bounce an dabs to the off side
thick edge that runs down to third man
eased down the ground, but straight to mid-on
this one's floated a touch ahead of the length area on middle, he deadbats that
pushed back to the bowler again, this was much fuller. Neesham was better of playing forward rather than defending from the crease
pressure building. This one's full on off, pushed to short cover
excellent bouncer, this one on middle and leg, Neesham ducks under it
shows the full face of the bat in defense
driven, but straight to Finch at cover point
back of a length on middle, worked on the back foot to midwicket
back of a length and outside off, opens the face and runs the ball to third man

good length on off, 147ks, Neesham hangs back and dabs it gently to the midwicket region. Cummins runs across, tracks it down, spins around, but misses a direct hit. Not by much. Neesham was struggling there
back of a length and straight in line, clipped away through square leg
144ks bouncer on leg, ducks under it
clipped off the pads square through the leg side
short on middle, hangs back and punches straight to midwicket
similar ball, punched to the left of midwicket
Head is firing it in, Neesham camps back and pushes to midwicket
shorter on middle, forced on the back foot to long-on
late-cut away to the left of point
dropped short and outside off, cut away to the right of Warner at sweeper cover
short on off, 145.2ks, fended back to the bowler
bouncer angling away outside off, 144.5ks, bursts past the hook. Wade leaps and gloves it over his head
back of a length and angling across off, stabbed to the covers
back of a length and outside off, Neesham stands tall and hits through the line. Punched away on the up between extra cover and point. First boundary by a NZ batsman other than Guptill
Cummins replies with a fiery bumper on middle, Neesham ducks late. Wade jumps and gloves it with one hand. Wide
back of a length and outside off, punched uppishly in the off-side gap
back of a length and outside off, opens the face and jabs to point
slider on off, poked towards point on the back foot
darted short and outside off, flat-batted away to long-on
whipped off the pads to square leg, where the fielder dives to his right, and takes some pace off the ball
speared into the pads, Neesham misses the flick. Might have inside-edged onto the pad
non-turning short ball, whipped on the back foot to midwicket
keeps it short, punched down to long-on
back of a length and angling away outside off, 147ks, run down to third man
back of a length and outside off, punched to point, diving save
nearly chopped on. Good length and on off, cross-seamer Williamson plays late, too late this time. Inside-edge bounces over off stump
stabbed into the off side
short and wide outside off, 146.2ks, Williamson can't find the gap, can't turn the strike. Cut straight to backward point
pitched up and outside off, driven on the up, but straight to extra cover
tossed up outside off, guided to short third man
short and speared in on middle, 94ks, hangs back and punches down to long-off
slides on off from around the stumps, back-foot force to long-on
short and skids on middle, punched to long-on again
fuller on the pads, flicked away to deep midwicket
straight roller on a fourth-stump line, opens the face and dabs the ball to point
full around off, clipped to deep midwicket
back of a length and outside off, crisply punched to sweeper cover
shot. Williamson needed this breathing space. NZ needed this breathing space. Full on off stump, hits through the line. Held the elbow up and lofted beautifully over mid-off
nurdled to the right of mid-on
back of a length, punched to mid-on
back of the hand slower ball outside off, <s>font size=72</s>, Neesham does not pick it. Throws his bat at a drive, does so early, skewing an outside edge to third man
skids on off, flat and speared in, whipped to midwicket
short and outside off, swiped away to midwicket again
much slower on off stump, skewed off the inside half to midwicket. Three dots, and the pressure builds on NZ again
tossed on middle, driven to the right of midwicket now
slides on off, worked straight to midwicket
pitched up on the stumps, played back to the bowler
back of a length and on the pads, clipped on the back foot to midwicket
full and slanting away outside off, Williamson, having shuffled across off, dabs to point
back of a length and outside off, steered to Hazlewood at third man
short and wide outside off, slapped away to the right of sweeper
back of a length and angling away outside off, chopped towards point
and the rising asking rate forces Williamson to manufacture a shot. He runs down the track, and chips it over mid-on for only the third boundary since Guptill's exit in the ninth over
speared short on off, the left-hander can't come forward. Stays back and punches to long-on
full on middle and leg, clipped to square leg
tossed up, Williamson backs away a touch and lifts it inside-out over mid-off
speared down leg, Williamson attempts a sweep, ends up gloving behind to the keeper. Could have been a wide
pushed outside leg again, Williamson goes low, pre-meditates a sweep, and finds long leg
whipped away to deep midwicket
slower delivery outside off, Neesham picks it. Waits for the ball to arrive and lofts it in the air between extra cover and mid-off
back of a length on off, flicked through the vacant spaces at midwicket. Warner stumbles a bit on the throw, sends the ball to the keeper's end, could have thrown to Williamson's end
full and outside off, slower from the back of the hand at 114ks, poked off an outside edge to point
back of a length and outside off, steered off the face to short third man
full and outside off, 110.7ks, hoicked away in the air over midwicket
short of a length on middle, goes back and runs the ball to point
good length on off, Williamson, blocked with a straight bat
back of a length and just outside off, Williamson shimmied out of the crease, but adjusts well. Plays late, opens the face, and secures a single down to third man
good length and angling away outside off, steered to backward point
good length and outside off, Neesham is through with the shot early against the slower ball. Chips the ball in front of long-on
good length and outside off, Williamson goes across the line. Slogs the ball over mid-on
back of a length and outside off, glides it neatly to third man
short and wide outside off, played, Williamson. Skips back and unleashes a strong square-cut
now Williamson brings out the glide to third man
full on off stump, pushed to point
full and outside off, aims a crease-bound drive, and drags an inside edge fine on the leg side, past the stumps
short and wide outside off, chops down to third man
full and outside off, Williamson drives without any feet and is beaten on the outside
full and just a shade outside off, the bat turns in the hands of Neesham. Wafted back to Marsh
back of a length on middle, played back to the bowler
full and wide outside off, driven with plenty of bottom hand to the right of extra cover
short ball on off, Neesham pulls. Tries to over-hit it and loses his shape. Ends up flapping the ball to square leg
bang! Neesham succeeds in pulling this. Dragged short and outside off, hammered away to the right of Finch at deep square leg. That exploded from the middle of the bat
back of a length and Marsh runs this across the left-hander, past the outside edge
glanced down to fine leg
short and wide outside off, Williamson reaches out for a wild slash and misses
yorker, speared in on off, from around the wicket. Jammed back
pitched up and outside off, driven through the line to mid-off
very full and outside off, guided down to third man
full and outside off, almost 148ks, dabbed wide of backward point
short and kicks up outside off, Neesham gets on top of the bounce and cuts powerfully to sweeper cover
finesse from Williamson. Employs the latest of late cuts. Played from outside off to third man
driven in the air to the left of mid-off. Good length and outside off, Neesham simply hits through the line. It's that kind of a pitch
hip-high short ball outside off, Neesham lays into it. Pulls it flat and hard over square leg, Finch had no chance running to his left from deep midwicket. Neesham acknowledges his fifty
back of a length and angling away outside off, crunched straight to mid-off
short on the hips, flicked away square through the leg side. Neesham wants two, but is sent back by his captain
back of a length and swings back into the left-hander, raps him on the pad, Neesham plays across, and is beaten for pace. Sliding down leg, though. Tinge of reverse for Starc
full-toss, swings away, pushed down to mid-off
full and reverse-swings in, squirted to midwicket
worked away to the right of midwicket

Neesham looks away, takes his eyes off it, and is struck flush on the unprotected part on his right forearm, just below the elbow. 148ks thunderbolt from Starc, Neesham misjudges the bounce, and ducks on the front foot, ouch! He barely flinches, however. Fiery short one from Starc, did not bounce as much as the batsman expected it to
full inswinging yorker, 147ks, Neesham just about digs it out
low full-toss on middle from around the stumps, hit down to long-on
shorter on off, punched on the back foot to long-on
flat and down leg, paddled fine past the keeper
Neesham skips out, Head adjusts his length. Short and speared on off. Fended
short and outside off, barely bail-high, pulled away to the cow corner fence
94.2ks, speared outside off, slashed in the air, "caaaatch" is the cry from Head. Does not carry to backward point
short and angled in, absorbed the pace on it and turned to the right of midwicket. Just one
full and outside off, nearly 149ks, driven to mid-off. Head can't throw the stumps down at the non-striker's end
very full and outside off, Williamson angles it down to third man
short of a length on off, hops and glides the ball down to third man
nice and full outside off, wristy drive to the left of extra cover
good length and tails in on off, run away to backward point
glanced off the pads to fine leg
slog-swept away to deep midwicket, more off the inside half of the bat
slides across Williamson, late-cut to short third man for a quick single
slog-swept away to Finch at deep square leg again
fired into the pads, whipped away to deep square leg. Williamson gets to a fifty of his own
darted on middle, no turn, swept away square through the leg side
back of a length and outside off, flat-bats a cut to sweeper
full on middle and leg, nudged to the right of midwicket
dug short and outside off, Neesham unleashes another rasping pull. Tonked away over midwicket
clipped off the hips through backward square leg for a couple
good length and angling away, played with soft hands to backward point

Hazlewood returns and takes down Neesham. Good length and angling away outside off, from over the wicket, Neesham can't get under it as this isn't as full as he would have liked. Aims a loft, and ends up skewing a catch to Starc moving back from mid-off. Neesham falls for 74, his best List A score
length and outside off, guided to sweeper cover
back of a length and outside off, back-foot force to deep point
length and outside off, driven to the covers
back of a length and outside off, punched to the covers
back of a length inducker, he aims to drive. Shoots through the gate. The ball bounces over the stumps
full and outside off, right in the hitting slot. Neesham was looking for this length. Munro gets it and dispatches the ball over the long-off boundary. Clean swing through the line
full and angled in on off, whipped away to deep square leg
back of a length, pitches on leg or just outside off, swings away, takes the outside edge and rolls to point
back of a length on off, punched to cover
short and angling away outside off, flashes and sends an outside edge to the left of lone slip
back of a length on middle, stabbed to cover
back of a length and swerving away, hops and fends to cover
back of a length and outside off, punched to the left of extra cover
short on middle, hops and fends
Holes out to long-on. Faulkner comes back and nabs Munro. Marsh completes a sprawling catch. Banged in short,  Munro commits to the front foot. Dares to pull and finds the fielder
short and angled in, picked off the hips to long leg
length and outside off, leans back and glides to third man
full on off, kept out
full and outside off, opens the face and dabs to third man
length ball on off, 140ks, reverses in a bit, pushed to mid-on
back of a length and outside off, jabbed to point
length ball snakes away outside off, past the outside edge
full and breaks back into the right-hander, he falls over and inside-edges it onto his pad
full, angled in, and then shapes away from de Grandhomme. He attempts a crease-bound drive and misses
length and outside off, punched to mid-off
Williamson steps out and shuffles outside leg, meets a short ball, and flat-bats it to extra cover
whipped from outside off over midwicket
short and angled in on off, opens the face and dabs the ball to backward point
and he gets off the mark with a six after eight balls. The batsman clears Bailey. Back of a length and outside off, swung away
back of the hand slower one outside off, chopped down towards third man
short on off, cramps him for room. Chopped to backward point
back of a length and angled in on off, defended with a straight bat
slower cutter outside off, 122ks, Williamson shuffles across and shovel-paddles it over short fine leg
down the track and slices an outside edge to third man
wide of the crease, and slanted it, raps the pad, and rolls away to square leg. It was definitely heading past the leg stump
short and outside off, late-cut to backward point, where Smith fumbles. He puts his hand up in apology right away
full and outside off, throws his hands at it and carves an outside edge to third man
short on off, pulled straight to midwicket. Williamson looking to over-hit the ball
Williamson pre-meditates, shuffles across off, takes it from outside off and paddles it fine of short fine leg. That's his first boundary since the 23rd over
follows it with a six. Back of a length on middle, heaved away over Cummins at deep square leg
slower short ball just outside off, chopped to short third man
back of the hand slower one outside off, Faulkner cuts this one across the right-hander. Wild slog-sweep and a miss

full and holds its line outside off, backs away and lifts it in the air. Bailey at extra cover dives to his left, the ball bursts through his hands to the boundary. Replays show that Bailey had finger-tipped it away
very full and angled in, driven down to mid-on
low full-toss outside off, sliced past backward point

edged and taken by Wade diving low to his right. Wide of the crease, very full and holds its line outside off. De Grandhomme does not move his feet, flashes a drive with his hands, and nicks behind. Excellent take from Wade
yorker, swerves down leg, wide
full-toss, tails into the pads, Santner is late to flick, and wears it on the top of the pad
very full and angled in, dropped to the covers with soft hands
short and wide outside off, cutter, 121ks. Williamson cuts on the back foot, and does so early. He can't keep it down either. Warner pockets the overhead catch at extra cover. Australia close in
Cummins greets him with a cross-seamer, rapid bouncer, ducks under it
back of a length and outside off, forced to sweeper cover
full on middle and leg, played back to the bowler
short of a length on middle, punched to extra cover for a scampered single
short and skids on off, 144ks, Wating throws his bat in front like a face-shield. Fended back
full on middle, driven on the front foot to long-on
full and holds its line outside off, Watling drives hard and misses
full and much wider outside off, Watling reaches out for a drive. Still can't make contact
Watling now succeeds in driving a full ball to deep covcer
144.5ks inswinging yorker from Starc. The result: Santner's stumps are left in a mess. Santner has a wild swish at it, but Starc is too quick for him
full on middle and leg, 148ks, hangs back and flicks to the right of mid-on
back of length delivery outside off, he backs away, frees his arms and smears it over point, one bounce into the boundary
uses the bowler's pace to glide it down to third man
backs away to slash over point but the steep bounce did him in. The ball also kept coming back in to cramp him for room
way too early into the pull, gets a bottom edge that goes through to Wade on the bounce

pace and bounce does the trick again. Southee was in no position to play a flat-batted pull. The ball got big on him, he was cramped for room and only managed to get a top edge to Bailey, who took a simple catch coming in from midwicket.
chopped behind the wicket and they scamper a run
firm push off the frontfoot but straight to cover
swung across the line, gets the toe end but the ball lands short of the man running in from long-off
stands still inside the crease and pushes the length ball to mid-off
how did that miss the off stump? I don't know. This one's fired full and into the stumps from around the stumps, the batsman went for an almighty thwack but missed it completely
juicy full toss that has been slashed over the infield to deep cover
play and a miss. This was too close to cut, the ball shaves past the inside edge
slower and fuller outside off, swung across the line to toe-end it towards deep square
off-cutter around the seventh stump, drags the slog from outside off towards midwicket. Didn't get it anywhere near the middle of the bat
excellent bouncer but way over the batsman's head. Watling did well to spot that early and duck under it
drilled down the ground but straight to Head at long-on
backs away to go over cover, but gets it off the toe end to the fielder there
swing and a miss. He looked to hit that to Sydney, but could only connect with the cool evening air. Went for a mow over cow corner but played too early
full-length delivery on off, driven to long-off
another swing and a miss. Backs away to slap that length ball over cover but he was nowhere near the ball
he can't lay bat on ball at the moment. Looks to swipe this over the infield, but the ball tails away late to beat his swing
three in a row. On another night, Starc would have shattered the stumps many times over. Floats this full and into the batsman from around the stumps, Henry swings over long-on but misses
backs away and lofts this one into the gap at cover, two it will be
looks for a yorker but turns out to be a high full toss on the body, tucked wide of midwicket as they take a single

hit well, but he's picked out the lone man at deep midwicket. Swung through the line to pull that short delivery, but it was almost as if he forgot there was a man in the deep. Nice, running catch from Faulkner. Ran to his left, was aware of the boundary behind him and pouched it safely. Hit and miss knock from Henry is over.
backs away and bunts an imcoming length ball to the off side
mistimes a pull to deep midwicket. Watling wanted the second but Boult wouldn't have made it back
right into the blockhole from wide of the crease, Boult just about manages to dig that out in the nick of time
punched to point from the crease
no, he can't. Excellent slower ball on middle, Boult gets an inside edge to the leg side and gets off the mark

swings and gets a thick inside edge towards the keeper. Watling was off the blocks, but Boult, who was ball-watching, had to really scamper through to make the crease even as the throw came whistling in to the bowler's end. A direct hit and he was gone.
that's a lovely hit. Backs away and slap the length ball over extra cover. The bat face slightly turned in his hand, but he ensured there was enough power
crunching drive, Boult was more than a couple of paces in for a run. Smith could have thrown it down at the bowler's end but he stopped short of doing that. May have cost Australia a run at max.
walks across the stumps and swings leg side, gets a bottom edge towards short fine leg
makes room and squeezes a yorker-length delivery to cover
clears his front leg and clobbers that to mid-off, calls 'wait' immediately. Can't beat the infield
slower delivery angling away, flayed to the point fielder

how fitting is it for Warner, the centurion, to take the catch? Australia have taken the Chappell-Hadlee series. Watling swings but doesn't get under that full delivery and ends up slicing it towards Warner, who circles around the ball briefly at cover, before settling underneath it to complete a comfortable catch.
